Vladimir Putin held a meeting with the leaders of State Duma factions. Vladimir Putin discussed with the heads of political parties the work plan for the next six years, the meeting was also attended by First Deputy Head of the Presidential Administration Sergei Kiriyenko and Chairman of the State Duma Vyacheslav Volodin. The President said that there is still a lot of stupidity and injustice in Russia, it is too early for the authorities to rest on their laurels - all parties need to work in a consolidated manner for the benefit of society and the state. The Russian leader noted that the government needs renewal not so much in specific people, but in approaches to solving problems.

Main theses of the faction representatives:

- Gennady Zyuganov asked Putin to make his first visit in the new presidential term not towards the West, but towards the East and come to China - Putin promised to fulfill his request;

— Sergei Mironov suggested that Putin consider awarding the governor of the Belgorod region Gladkov, as well as creating an agency for veterans’ affairs and a ministry of demography;

— Leonid Slutsky proposed not to collect income tax from people whose salaries are up to ₽30 thousand, he also voiced the idea of issuing combat veteran certificates to military officers who work in the special operation zone.

At the end of the meeting, Vyacheslav Volodin spoke and conveyed congratulations to Putin on his victory in the elections from the parliamentary delegation of the Republika Srpska.

